Distribution . Mountains of the Sierra Huichola, in the municipality of Bolaños, Jalisco , with forests of pine, oak and oyamel, located between 2250–2300 m ( Fig. 5 ). The Sierra Huichola is considered a “Prioritary Land Region” for conservation, with high endemism, but has been significantly altered by extensive severe fragmentation of natural habitat (
Arriaga et al . 2000
).
